#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:3
#: e2a7093540fd43a991946850bd457d6f
msgid "How to upgrade a Debian template in-place"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:7
#: 1aadf85a14054abbad1ea2b218344f4f
msgid "This page is intended for advanced users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:11
#: a13f59225de34d96b9f200ebcdbc179b
msgid ""
"**Warning:** This page is intended for advanced users only. Most users "
"seeking to upgrade should instead :ref:`install a new Debian template "
"<user/templates/debian/debian:installing>`. Learn more about the two "
"options :ref:`here <user/templates/debian/debian:upgrading>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:13
#: 6b4c1abb54bd49b489c17428165d0879
msgid ""
"This page provides instructions for performing an in-place upgrade of an "
"installed :doc:`Debian Template </user/templates/debian/debian>`. If you "
"wish to install a new, unmodified Debian template instead of upgrading a "
"template that is already installed in your system, please see the "
":doc:`Debian Template </user/templates/debian/debian>` page instead. "
"(:ref:`Learn more about the two options. "
"<user/templates/debian/debian:upgrading>`) In general, upgrading a Debian"
" template follows the same process as `upgrading a native Debian system "
"<https://wiki.debian.org/DebianUpgrade>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:16
#: e28ae6f25eae4a99b21f3d3a16c168e8
msgid "Summary instructions for Debian templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:19
#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:41
#: 62c0e16bd9044148a853bc2aa2412ffd dc1f837edce340278b16969cf8b97519
msgid ""
"**Important:** The prompt on each line indicates where each command "
"should be entered: ``dom0``, ``debian-<old>``, or ``debian-<new>``, where"
" ``<old>`` is the Debian version number *from* which you are upgrading, "
"and ``<new>`` is the Debian version number *to* which you are upgrading. "
"The instructions may differ for certain releases. See `release-specific "
"notes <#release-specific-notes>`__ for any instructions specific to your "
"particular release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:33
#: 1d9a67dfd09047ebb502d2c67b649a92
msgid ""
"**Recommended:** :ref:`Switch everything that was set to the old template"
" to the new template. <user/templates/templates:switching>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:36
#: e82635f63c0345699f5605297d02177f
msgid "Detailed instructions for Debian templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:39
#: 4e71ffde2b0640ff89ad17ee155b57a8
msgid ""
"These instructions will show you how to upgrade Debian templates. The "
"same general procedure may be used to upgrade any template based on the "
"standard Debian template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:43
#: 4e08eabdb78f4d1c842ac21c6a54b041
msgid "Ensure the existing template is not running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:50
#: d9edf6b6d85c4a6592ea3d3e5229c38f
msgid "Clone the existing template and start a terminal in the new template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:58
#: cfbbe571485b4d95ad06d2807fdfd7b4
msgid ""
"Update your ``apt`` repositories to use the new release’s code name "
"instead of the old release’s code name. (This can be done manually with a"
" text editor, but ``sed`` can be used to automatically update the files.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:67
#: ae7870c789bc43d98a797f8e8f31d51c
msgid ""
"Update the package lists and upgrade. During the process, it may prompt "
"you to overwrite the file ``qubes-r4.list``. You should overwrite this "
"file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:77
#: a950f00ec5b643d79c306b1b5fcd0642
msgid "(Optional) Remove unnecessary packages that were previously installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:85
#: 9031eb57f2834593adc1d893c9d02ed7
msgid "(Optional) Clean cached packages from ``/var/cache/apt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:93
#: 2cc20e4e5f854e81bfd9560fe9c302a9
msgid ""
"(Optional) Trim the new template. (This should :ref:`no longer be "
"necessary <user/templates/templates:important notes>`, but it does not "
"hurt. Some users have `reported <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/5055>`__ that it makes a difference.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:103
#: cb71e6a49fe244b9a0ff0580f188d60b
msgid "Shut down the new template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:110
#: 00661e382af84a96909221bb19442375
msgid ""
"(Recommended) :ref:`Switch everything that was set to the old template to"
" the new template. <user/templates/templates:switching>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:112
#: 8b21afe2983e4067b738f8967095c712
msgid "(Optional) Make the new template the global default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:119
#: 30554f4b11724009ab26365e03d239e1
msgid ""
"(Optional) :ref:`Uninstall the old template. "
"<user/templates/templates:uninstalling>` Make sure that the template "
"you’re uninstalling is the old one, not the new one!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:124
#: 52819d2460854fdabf286bb742120115
msgid "Standalones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:127
#: 81a386c4b082420e97031b80a0c44169
msgid ""
"The procedure for upgrading a Debian :doc:`standalone </user/advanced-"
"topics/standalones-and-hvms>` is the same as for a template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:130
#: bd5f3a7b4ad94bd69148282e0523467f
msgid "Release-specific notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:133
#: 2683cce14f1e451ea05984810dd84ee9
msgid "This section contains notes about upgrading to specific releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:136
#: 0305e717a728474dbf49db3b5caa4a8f
msgid "Debian 11 (\"Bullseye\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:139
#: 876e6fce83f445e29005d5a3b48c107b
msgid ""
"Please see `Debian’s Bullseye upgrade instructions "
"<https://www.debian.org/releases/bullseye/amd64/release-notes/ch-"
"upgrading.en.html>`__. In particular: for APT source lines referencing "
"the security archive, the format has changed slightly along with the "
"release name, going from buster/updates to bullseye-security; see "
"`Section 5.1.2, “Changed security archive layout” "
"<https://www.debian.org/releases/stable/mips64el/release-notes/ch-"
"information.en.html#security-archive>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:141
#: 5a265e86e9f140589ca794651c945db7
msgid ""
"This means that, when upgrading from Buster to Bullseye, an additional "
"``sed`` command is required:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:157
#: a68f9a5c954f4a13b84f01fdb7ab8765
msgid "Debian 10 (\"Buster\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:160
#: daa305b7e60a4629965ee98e1003b617
msgid ""
"Please see `Debian’s Buster upgrade instructions "
"<https://www.debian.org/releases/buster/amd64/release-notes.en.txt>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:163
#: b053804942b0464a8776cafcf0051c4c
msgid "Debian 9 (\"Stretch\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:166
#: 937151010952401e928a77d40310b238
msgid ""
"The upgrade process may prompt you to overwrite two files: "
"``qubes-r4.list`` and ``pulse/client.conf``. ``qubes-r4.list`` can be "
"overwritten, but ``pulse/client.conf`` must be left as the currently-"
"installed version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:168
#: 9462157e42dc457e93e3ec0eae7467e2
msgid ""
"If sound is not working, you may need to enable the Qubes testing "
"repository to get the testing version of ``qubes-gui-agent``. This can be"
" done by editing the ``/etc/apt/sources.list.d/qubes-r4.list`` file and "
"uncommenting the ``Qubes Updates Candidates`` repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/debian/debian-upgrade.rst:170
#: 7b93bf547b1f4beba0ec1a23eb0f72b7
msgid ""
"User-initiated updates/upgrades may not run when a template first starts."
" This is due to a new Debian config setting that attempts to update "
"automatically; it should be disabled with ``sudo systemctl disable apt-"
"daily.{service,timer}``."
msgstr ""

